## Context

Follow-on to PR #718. `content/technical-report.qmd` still contains three framing
sections as inline prose: Overview, Standardisation (Z-scores), and Summary of
findings. Extracting these into `_includes/techrep/` makes the TR a pure
composer of includes (YAML header + four include lines), so any future document
(zoo-only, summary-only, overview+zoo, etc.) can cherry-pick subsets.

## Actions

1. Create `content/_includes/techrep/` directory.
2. Copy the Overview section verbatim into `overview.md`.
3. Copy the Standardisation section verbatim into `zscore.md`.
4. Copy the Summary of findings section verbatim into `summary-of-findings.md`.
5. Rewrite the TR body to four `{{< include ... >}}` lines.

## Test

Render equivalence: `quarto render content/technical-report.qmd --to html`
yields the same `##` heading structure as before. Grep for `{{< meta ... >}}`
vars returns the same set pre/post.

## Exit criteria

- `content/_includes/techrep/{overview,zscore,summary-of-findings}.md` exist.
- `content/technical-report.qmd` body is the four include lines only.
- No substantive headings remain in the TR body.
- Each include file begins with exactly one top-level heading.
